name: YSL Cafe
reviews: [{'author': 'Johnny Vincent', 'text': "I wish I could say I had a positive experience at this unique Saint Laurent location, but the way the staff treated me has left me contemplating shopping there again. I visited specifically to purchase exclusive items only available at this store, and it quickly became evident that they didn't value my business. When I requested the items I wanted to buy, the representative went to the back to retrieve them but then proceeded to assist another customer, completing their purchase and letting them leave, all while I was left waiting for my items. After nearly 20 minutes and witnessing numerous customers entering and leaving with similar items much faster, I finally received my purchases. Finally, I received my items, but the damage was done. As I was leaving, I spotted another item I wanted, and suddenly, two new representatives were all too eager to assist me, probably because it was a high-priced item. This blatant favoritism and disregard for my time and loyalty as a customer have left me seriously reconsidering whether I'll ever shop at YSL again.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': 1698753251000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101441535972946575598/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Ravioli Folie

name: JJAN
reviews:
[{'author': 'Carla Escobar', 'text': 'Food looks delicious but is somehow tasteless.
The kimchi pancake is extra oily.
The service was nice and friendly.
Overall atmosphere is loud and fun, good for an affordable dinner with friends if you are in the area and don’t care much for the food quality.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': 1707424949000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114297807640926292578/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

Waited 30 minutes for one bowl.', 'rating': '2', 'date_published': 1711806203000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101222910970459002220/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Libshop
reviews: [{'author': 'Daphné Fourcault', 'text': "11€ for 3 falafels and green salad. Everything is bathed in an ocean of vinegar. I won't set foot there again.", 'rating': '1', 'date_published': 1679322691000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106236456018101817744/reviews', 'lang': 'fr'}]

name: CÈPE ET FIGUE
reviews:
[{'author': 'Karla Miranda', 'text': 'Of all the times I’ve been in Paris, this is the best Parisian food I’ve had. I found this place just like that and I didn’t regret it.

Me and my husband chose the three course menu (29€ great price!) and it was just heaven. The onion soup felt like a grandma soup, the lamb was so soft and tasty and the dessert was just amazing.

Please come to this place! The food and the service is great, very very recommended.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1690973182000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114218307343670470619/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Genki 元気
reviews: [{'author': 'Dan G', 'text': "I had the fraise cheese. The best strawberry boba that I've ever had in any country I've been to. Wennic Greeted me with a smile and kept that smile the whole time we were there.  Amazing service, amazing place.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1704463407000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107721890758487260313/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Maison Louvard
reviews: [{'author': 'arnaud vanderroost', 'text': "I saw this bakery on Social Media and was curious to know why people were given such a high rate to this place. I wanted to check it by myself 😉 The place is cozy and well decorated. The staff is super friendly and the 'viennoiserie' tasteful. The expresso is also really good and compared to other places in the capital, your getting a decent amount of coffee in your cup (not only a few drops). It was good, but wouldn't given them a 5 star rate (even if the bakker has apparently received an award recently). Guess I will have to go a second time (at lunch) to confirm my thoughts... A place to recommend anyhow.", 'rating': '4', 'date_published': 1706266344000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109582078903072481714/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Pasticeria Simona
reviews: [{'author': 'tejbir kaur sohal', 'text': 'One of the best places to find authentic Italian pastries!! Must try their Maritozzo and Biaocchi!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1709035942000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113896681132813905584/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Trantranzai
reviews:
[{'author': 'Frank Mansell', 'text': 'Very tasty food here.

I went for the ravioli noodle soup, with the highest possible spice (8), and I wasn’t disappointed. It was incredibly flavoursome, and it was actually spicy compared to a lot of other noodle soups in Paris. If you like chillis, go for this level! It doesn’t blow your head off, but leaves a lovely refreshing tingle and a warm mouth.

The Tsingtao beer alongside it was great, and the restaurant itself is lovely.

Thank you very much, I’ll be back', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1699830125000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/116117366506923146791/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: KINGKONG
reviews: [{'author': 'Josh Rennert', 'text': 'Unfortunately, they stopped serving their corndogs, but the food was delicious all the same! A nice Korean restaurant near Sentier, with a cool upstairs ambiance. Recommended!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1658528418000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101793772923497739852/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Flam&go
reviews: [{'author': 'M H', 'text': 'I discovered this address yesterday and I am delighted with this moment. I opted for a brunch which, in addition to being very good, was plentiful. I was able to leave with the dessert which I was unable to finish. The atmosphere is a little noisy but it would be a shame to stop at that detail. I recommend !', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1710167103000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103959454148932882405/reviews', 'lang': 'fr'}]

name: Afri Call Food
reviews: [{'author': 'Eva Spileers', 'text': 'Super 👍', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1705236030000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103074173252837124459/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Keopi
reviews:
[{'author': 'Roxana M.Nejad', 'text': 'The location is simply great, not too far from the Grevin museum ! You really get to feel the parisian vibe.
The price was reasonable for a brunch + it was really delicious. The staff is also really nice and attentive.
We went for a kimchi and avocado salmon toast (which if you like salty and spicy kimchi is a perfect match with avocado and salmon). The Rose Latte was too die for with its hint of rose taste. The spicy chicken was really soft (a perfect boneless chicken if I dare say).
And for the dessert the waffle with matcha cream ! The cream paired perfectly with the fruits and the waffle ~ Beware though, the plate is kind of big so if you don’t have a big appetite it is best to share it.

All in all the pricing, the amount of food and the taste was more than worthy, a 10/10 for me.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1696435553000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103704298572361074866/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Land & monkeys
reviews: [{'author': 'Jaspreet Singh', 'text': "What a most lovely vegan bakery! We stumbled upon it while researching vegan eats in Paris, and honestly it was so good we went back the next day! The sandwiches were SO good, as was the quiche and various pastries. I am not vegan, however my husband is, and it was so amazing to be able to eat traditional Parisian pastries together and not feel like one is missing out. We bought so many pastries as well to go and were snacking on them throughout the trip! The cookies were also very delicious and so worth try! Marion was an absolute sweetheart both days, and was so patient as we tried to speak in our broken French to order. She gave many amazing recommendations and we can't wait to come back and visit!", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1710184510000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105087097158667648334/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Boneshaker Donuts
reviews:
[{'author': 'Amina Panduru', 'text': 'I am soo amazed that this place is vegan, you really can’t tell! The apple donut is autumn 🍂 in a donut ♥️ so fluffy and amazing flavour combo!

The owners also are very cute and kind!

Will be back!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1699138181000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108674275854574740720/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: OYA Fusion
reviews: [{'author': 'Yann GORRA DIALLO', 'text': 'Service on point and atmosphere just dope. Great DJ. I strongly recommend.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': 1703747272000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111516157611346316670/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: ACÀ PIGALLE
reviews: [{'author': 'María Fernanda Vidal Correa', 'text': 'Overall, is a good place to eat tacos considering you are in Paris. Formule of three tacos for 10€ is a great option. Good flavor in the barbacoa, pastor a little dry, and carnitas would improve with a little more coriander. Sauces are good and tasty, not super spicy. Agua de horchata is super good, not too sweat which I like.  However, the dessert, the pastel de tres leches, falls short of expectations. While sweet and pastry-like, it lacks the authentic essence of a true pastel de tres leches.', 'rating': '4', 'date_published': 1710939078000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109498612452677260127/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Café Louis Vuitton
reviews: [{'author': 'Deniss Ovčarenko', 'text': "Probably the most delicious cake I've ever ate! We got the chocolate and vanilla ones and they were amazing!\nPretty pricey, but understandable - it's Louis Vuitton!\nStaff was amazing, very friendly and very caring, smiling! Will definitely return when back in Paris", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1703713014000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110313350747670160192/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Puffy Cookies
reviews: [{'author': 'Melissa W', 'text': 'This is not a normal cookie, it’s thick and gooey. The chocolate and peanut butter one was my favourite.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1709482959000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100714489852644028525/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Maison Maé
reviews: [{'author': 'Eva Ottum', 'text': 'My 3 friends and I are visiting Paris as Americans for the first time and this cafe is the most amazing part of Paris. Friendly staff, who have been helping us with our French, tasty food at a reasonable price, and a relaxing atmosphere. We’ve come here every morning and will definitely come again the next time we visit! I’d recommend the ham escargot and the espresso! They also gave our group free pastries sometimes :)', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1705399300000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115132071909847691921/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Bao Express
reviews: [{'author': 'Rob Wise', 'text': 'This has to be one of THE HIDDEN GEMS of Paris. This isn’t on any tourist lists of places to eat and it’s not typical French food, but it is delicious and the vibe in this place is immaculate. We enjoyed it so much, we went back on our last night in Paris to have it again!  Beef Ho Fun is easily the best dish we had in Paris and the Sweet and Sour Chicken is unlike any version we’ve had in the best way possible. Also, if you’re a dessert person, the lava French toast is a must try!  We would eat here again and again and will recommend this place to anyone traveling to Paris!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1695294145000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106420206648122939671/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Kous
reviews: [{'author': 'Sophia Divita', 'text': 'This place was THE BEST! I met the owner Bader and he was super nice. A must try if you’re in Paris!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1694098364000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103923188364073001947/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: GYOZA HOUSE
reviews:
[{'author': 'Elias Abou Haydar', 'text': 'For me, it’s easy. If you feel like eating gyozas, you need to come to this place.

It’s the best gyozas you can find in the city.

The service is nice and very polite.

You won’t be disappointed. I highly recommend.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1698867672000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105336789334033682765/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: CHEZ HAKI
reviews: [{'author': 'Micayla Ramos', 'text': 'The food was incredible. Tender noodles with the perfect chew with rich delicious broth. We loved the S7! The service was excellent and the atmosphere cozy. A perfect rich and hearty meal at very reasonable prices especially for the flavor, portions, and quality.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1712093361000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105572440024582186664/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: RAMEN WANG
reviews: [{'author': 'Monica Rivera', 'text': 'Everything was delicious! Ramen was amazing with lots of flavors. The veggie gyozas as appetizers were tasty too. Nice variety of desserts and I really recommend the matcha financiers with ginger ice cream. Nice wine by the glass as well. Very cozy venue and ambience. A must!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1675549566000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107074390665313624214/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Mopa
reviews: [{'author': 'Fran Pilkington-Cheney', 'text': 'Great little vegan place. Food was very tasty, service was brilliant. We had the cheeseburger, bacon burger and Berliner kebap with fries. Good came quickly, not greasy at all. Red wine was a good accompaniment!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1693599448000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/114140047473939069331/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Maslow - Restaurant Paris 1
reviews: [{'author': 'Katarina H', 'text': 'Best meal in Paris by far. Kid approved as well! The service, ambience and food quality was superb. Our waiter Alex was so kind and attentive. He made just the perfect recommendations. We are looking forward to coming back! Merci beaucoup!!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1711743897000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112399567715751525668/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: LiBeyrouth
reviews: [{'author': 'Theo Sayad', 'text': 'We went for the 20€ buffet and there was a long queue but we decided to wait. We got seated in a bit of a tight space but the Lebanese staff were super friendly and welcoming and offered us drinks and desserts. The food was also of high quality, and overall, it was a nice experience. Would definitely recommend, worth the wait.', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1712411519000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102913402663645081832/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Marcus Pizze Amore
reviews: [{'author': 'Stephanie Safdie', 'text': 'Super friendly staff and AMAZING vegan pizza. The vegan tiramisu was also amazing. Would 10/10 eat here again!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1710501388000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107495179346255478258/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Jungle Palace
reviews:
[{'author': 'Marie Mac', 'text': "Def must visit , loved the ambience and the Pulled Pork Burger was amazing .also recommend the eggplant for starter !!! The Banoffee desert was lovely and light and we all enjoyed the whole experience.
Service was super attentive and smiling all the time , making our visit memorable. Dishes were well explained to us as well. In particular, our waitress named Aure was very sweet and knows her job to a tee.

Only comment for restaurant was that at some point the music was a little repetitive. But didn't bother me that much but just something to consider", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1709665317000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106156906629811144400/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Plan D - DWICH & GLACE
reviews: [{'author': 'Valentine B', 'text': "Plan D is a haven for vegetarian/vegan sandwich enthusiasts.\nIt's a blast to find a place where you can eat vegan without feeling like you're left with the side dish. Highly recommended for anyone seeking a delicious and satisfying experience that leaves a lasting impression.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1711452808000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105173715322746306920/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: La Piadineria

name: Green Farmer's Paris
reviews:
[{'author': 'Amina Panduru', 'text': 'One of the best vegan burgers ever! If you feed this to a non vegetarian, for sure he will not notice 🤫

I got the chichen burger and I loved it! Onion rings were too greasy though.
The truffle mayo sauce was wow!

It’s great that this place is open even between lunch and dinner when many restaurants close. 🎉', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1699136352000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108674275854574740720/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Marvely
reviews: [{'author': 'April Welch', 'text': 'Amazing atmosphere with food that will make your tastebuds feel magical. If you are looking for a breakfast that’s next level please go here. Staff is very pleasant!!!', 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1696245680000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109574132705249024580/reviews', 'lang': 'en'}]

name: Tableaux Paris
reviews:
[{'author': 'Agnes Mougin', 'text': "We took Tableaux for the catering part of my son's baptism and I can tell you that everything was absolutely PERFECT!!!
The guests were amazed by both the beauty of the buffet and the quality of the products tasted.
I would add that the entire team is extremely kind and professional. Logistics is simple, reliable, fluid.
In short, I recommend with your eyes closed.", 'rating': '5', 'date_published': 1678986797000, 'author_profile_url': 'https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100666471020569089959/reviews', 'lang': 'fr'}]
